At the end of March 2009, the debt to suppliers amounted to about 14 billion rubles. For 9 months of 2009, production fell by 43.5% compared to the corresponding period of the previous year. ., which, in turn, in the form of an interest-free loan for a period of a year, will transfer to AvtoVAZ OJSC.[25]
Also, the model range of AvtoVAZ OJSC fell under the state program for subsidizing interest rates on car loans.[26]
In September 2009, the company's management announced a massive staff reduction: by the end of 2009, they were going to cut 27.6 thousand jobs.